mediaNotes: Calling for a high perch right at the parking lot as the sun was coming up.  No wind, and little background noise made for a very good recording of the whistle song
Nice example of the chick-a-dee-dee-dee-dee calls typical for this area.

singing perhaps 15' high & 30' away. Was just upstream from Gradyville Rd bridge. 6:40 am   Sunrise was 6:46 am
clean recording except stream noise.  In listening it may be 2 birds. I didn't notice at the time

Early morning song and conversation between the 2 Chickadees.  Near the end of this recording, one of the Carolina Chickadees was atop his nest box singing loudly.  There can also be heard Northern Cardinal, Carolina Wren, human (me) walking, wind sounds, and American Robin towards the end.  Giving these birds their space as they are breeding.  Not getting too close to the nest box area but still a beautiful song.
